      "raw_text": "The city of Spokane has re-\nceived from the Priest River Pow\ner company an offer for supplying\nof light to the city by that com\npany at rate of 6 cents per kilo-\nwatt hour, which is cents cheaper\nthan local consumers are now pay\ning, and for supplying power at a\nrate of about $3.50 per horsepower,\nor So per horsepower cheaper than\nis being paid the Washington\nWater Power company.\n\n\nSeveral members of the council\nlook up on the proposition with IA\nfor, and it is expected that the\nproposition will be taken up for\ndiscussion at the next regular\nmeeting of the council."
